&lt;Fletcher Challenge Ltd> (FCL)chairman Ron Trotter will step aside as chief executive inOctober on reaching 60 and will be replaced by group managingdirector Hugh Fletcher, FCL said in a statement.    Fletcher, 39, whose grandfather James Fletcher was thefounder of &lt;Fletcher Industries> from which FCL partly takesits name, joined the group in 1969.    He holds master of commerce, bachelor of science and MBAdegrees from Harvard University and is also chairman of Air NewZealand. No new managing director has been named yet to replacehim. REUTER&#3;